physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Laceration, 3 cm in length, along the left parietal occipital region. Pupils 4 mm in diameter, equal, round, and reactive to light. No trauma to face, no crepitus in neck soft tissue, trachea midline. Jugular venous pressure could not be assessed. Normal examination of chest, heart, abdomen. Normal rectal tone, stool negative for occult blood. Well perfused arms and legs with normal pulses. No spinal deformities or trauma.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: At initial examination, the patient did not respond to verbal or physical stimulation but began responding to noxious stimuli shortly after arrival, implying improvement in consciousness.
